  • java.lang.Object
    • stocktrader.StockQuote
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class StockQuote
extends java.lang.Object

    A class that holds all information given in a stock quote.

    • Constructor Detail

      • StockQuote

        public StockQuote()
        Constructor that is mainly used as a safety feature. It alerts the program (or whatever method needs something from it) that the StockQuote being fetched is invalid.

      • StockQuote

        public StockQuote(java.lang.String name,
                  java.lang.String symbol,
                  float daysLow,
                  float daysHigh,
                  float yearLow,
                  float yearHigh,
                  float open,
                  float realtime_price,
                  float change_percent,
                  java.lang.String timeStamp)
        This is the constructor that demonstrates the valid way to initialize a StockQuote object. It takes in all the information about a particular stock quote and stores said information.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the company.
        symbol - the ticker symbol of the company.
        daysLow - the reported lowest price of the most recent day.
        daysHigh - the reported highest price of the most recent day.
        yearLow - the reported lowest price of the past year.
        yearHigh - the reported highest price of the past year.
        open - the reported opening price of the most recent day.
        realtime_price - the current price of the stock.
        change_percent - the current change in price of the stock.
        timeStamp - the time at which the stock quote was obtained.
